result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy G. Crary was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Conditions:  Attend, pay for, and successfully complete any education or counseling ordered by the agent.  Costs have been ordered remitted by the Court.

16CM100 - Count 1 - 6 mo jail, imposed/stayed for probation of 2 years.  2 days credit in the event of revocation.  Costs.

16CM133 - Count 2 - 30 days jail, imposed/stayed, concurrent with 16CM100 and 16CM140's imposed/stayed jail for 2 years probation.  

16CM140 - Count 1 - 6 mo jail, imposed/stayed, consecutive to 16CM100 jail, for probation of 2 years.

Conditions of probation:  Pay one set of costs (16CM100).  Pay for, attend, and successfully complete any education/counseling ordered by agent.  Attend, pay for, and successfully complete 24- or 26-week d.a. class during the 2-year probation term.
